tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE public_transport_usage (
    user_id INT,
    route_id INT,
    date DATE,
    fare DECIMAL,
    distance_traveled DECIMAL
);

CREATE TABLE public_transportation_data (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id UUID,
    vehicle_id UUID,
    start_location TEXT,
    end_location TEXT,
    distance_km FLOAT,
    travel_time_min INTEGER
);

CREATE TABLE vehicle_details (
    vehicle_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    vehicle_type TEXT,
    manufacturer TEXT,
    model TEXT,
    year INTEGER
);

CREATE TABLE public_transportation_system (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  city_name VARCHAR(50),
  transportation_type VARCHAR(50),
  carbon_emission FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE transportation_logs (
  log_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id INT,
  transportation_id INT,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP,
  distance_traveled FLOAT
)

CREATE TABLE user_profiles (
  user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  username VARCHAR(50),
  email VARCHAR(50),
  age INT
)

CREATE TABLE Transportation_Stations (
    station_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    station_name VARCHAR(255),
    city VARCHAR(100),
    latitude DECIMAL(9,6),
    longitude DECIMAL(9,6)
)

CREATE TABLE Transportation_Routes (
    route_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    route_name VARCHAR(255),
    route_type VARCHAR(50),
    start_station_id INT,
    end_station_id INT
)

CREATE TABLE Transportation_Tickets (
    ticket_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    passenger_name VARCHAR(255),
    route_id INT,
    ticket_price DECIMAL(8,2),
    purchase_date DATE
)

CREATE TABLE Transportation_Analytics (
    analytics_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    route_id INT,
    passengers_count INT,
    carbon_emission DECIMAL(10,2),
    analysis_date DATE
)
